  "description": [
    "A VOL 24 NO 26 Capital Spotlight by CHARLOTTE WEBER Copyright 1948 JTA Inc WASHINGTON After considerable delay the Senate Immigration Subcommit tee has begun a broad investiga tion of every phase of U S immi gration and naturalization policy If any action results from the subcommittee study this will be the first time U S immigration policy has been overhauled since 1924 when the present rigid sys tem was enacted into law Not so long ago in 1945 an other Congressional committee studied the problem and concluded that there was widespread ignor ance about U S immigration laws and procedures The House Im migration Committee headed by New York Democrat Samuel Dickstein made its report late in November 1945 They found that the immigration laws are clearly in need of thorough study looking toward complete codification re gardless of whether substantive changes are thought to be re quired They suggested that no changes in existing quota pro visions or the selection of immi grants be made until the study was completed They also made some minor recommendations concerning immigration and de portation procedures but few have been carried out The present investigation was authorized by a Senate resolution passed"
  ],
